oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: J.P. Brownlow and Son General Store
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of seven unidentified people standing outside of J.P. Brownlow and Son General Store. There is a display in each of the windows. The store was located on the east side of the public square in Mount Pleasant. Note: this image appears on one and a half negatives.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Stores & shops; People; Merchandise displays
